Just Sold - 851 San Vicente #121
West Hollywood, CA
1 Bed 1 Bath - 930sqft
$755,000.00
 
Welcome to one of the most coveted buildings in West Hollywood, The Desmond. Located in the ultra desirable Norma Triangle area of West Hollywood, this Mediterranean gem boasts oasis like courtyards with lush landscaping, mature olive trees, and numerous fountains. Located on the main level of the building, this single story corner unit features an open layout with an entry, dining and living with fireplace and high ceilings, flooded with natural light coming through all the windows and glass doors to your very own private and expansive wraparound patio, providing the finest California lifestyle experience. The large kitchen, ideal for entertaining, showcases granite countertops, tile flooring, and ample cabinet space, along with stainless steel appliances and in unit laundry. With its easy flow, the open floor plan offers an ample bedroom suite with its walk-in closet and recently remodeled bathroom, also accessible from the living area for your guests. This very special offering is the ultimate getaway within the heart of the city, located a stone throw from all the best West Hollywood has to offer.

Just Sold - 4221 Greenbush
Sherman Oaks, CA
4 Beds 3 Baths - 1,650sqft
$1,575,000.00

Stunning and recently remodeled single level home on quiet tree lined street in prime Sherman Oaks . Gated, hedged & private, this home was taken down to the studs, & redesigned w/ high end finishes. Offering an ADU w/ a separate address & entrance, this is the perfect opportunity for a guest house, home office or for generating rental income. The main home boasts 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, pitched ceilings, skylights, stylish fireplace & a gorgeous chefs kitchen w/ marble countertops. One of the guest bedrooms is outfitted with beautiful bifold doors providing easy access to the entertainers yard. The primary en suite bedroom also has direct access to the spool & spacious yard w/ turf, fire pit and built in covered BBQ. This rare offering is ideally located near Ventura Boulevard and its dining and shopping experiences as well as the renowned Dixie Canyon Community Charter Elementary.
Naughty or not, here we come

Just Sold - 3906 Tracy
Los Feliz, CA
3 Beds 3 Baths - 1,947sqft
$1,750,00.00

This very special, newly renovated Los Feliz home draws influence from midcentury design and features warm, modern updates. Spaciousness and fantastic flow are accented by designer finishes and pitched ceilings throughout the living room and dining area, with walnut wood accent wall and decorative fireplace. The heart of the home is the lovely kitchen with eat-in island and cozy seating area. Newly renovated and set below skylights, the kitchen features Kitchenaid appliance package, custom walnut cabinetry, designer glazed tile, and pantry. Through a private hallway and past the large walk-in closet, the bright primary suite is revealed featuring beamed ceilings, private entrance to the backyard and fabulous bathroom with freestanding soaking tub, shower, and custom dual sink vanity with designer lighting. Two guest bedrooms with ample closet space, designer bathrooms, and a separate laundry room with sink complete the 1,947sf plan. A covered deck opens to the side yard for dining and entertaining. The grassy backyard features an additional seating area set among new landscaping and persimmon trees. Oversized two car garage plus gated driveway parking and drought tolerant landscaped front yard complete this fabulous offering. Additional features are new electrical and panel upgrade, updated plumbing, new heater and AC, new hot water heater, roof, flooring, windows, doors, and stucco. Situated in the Franklin Hills, a tree lined neighborhood with lots of community spirit, moments from Gelson's and shopping and dining along Hyperion Ave. and in Los Feliz Village. Located in coveted Franklin Elementary school district.
🎶 Hey now, I’m an All Star 🎶

Walls of glass slide open to a grassy yard with lush vegetation and sweeping canyon views. 3 bedrooms, 3 baths, and a breezy courtyard complete this wonderful oasis.

⁣

West Hollywood, CA 
2 Beds 2 Baths - 1,482sqft
$1,099,000

In the heart of West Hollywood, this single-level residence offers elevated design and was tastefully curated to create a sophisticated lifestyle experience. With two beds, two baths plus a den, enjoy a sun drenched completely remodeled modern organic open layout, across nearly 1,500 sqft, with a south facing view looking towards the Pacific Design Center. The stunning brand new kitchen features built in appliances, ample cabinet space, in-unit laundry and opens up to the expansive living area with it's clay finished fireplace and large balcony.The secondary bedroom has a Jack n Jill bath that serves as a powder for your guests, and the den, which could be used in many other unique options such as office or formal dining is ideally located just off the public spaces. The oversized primary suite is completed with three closets and a refined en-suite bathroom. Located in the boutique Palm Terrace building, with amenities such as pool, spa, recreation room and two side by side parking, minutes to the best West Hollywood has to offer.

Just Sold - 3663 Homeland
View Park , CA 
4 Beds - 3 Baths
2,368sqft
$1,950,000

Nestled in the rolling hills of View Park, is this two-story, 4BD/3BA colonial estate. Upon walking through the front door, you immediately feel the welcoming sense of home and warmth. The formal living room is bright and spacious, with light flowing in through bay windows, and boasts a character fireplace, designer sconces, fresh hardwood floors. Off the living room, you'll find the sun room, offering views of the expansive tiered backyard through oversized windows, the perfect office nook or den. The open concept kitchen features elegant soapstone counters, complemented by a Calacatta gold marble backsplash, "greige" cabinets and brushed brass hardware. All new stainless steel appliances, including double oven and peninsula cooktop, will make those holiday dinners a breeze. The dining area feels spacious, boasting modern brass lighting and sliding door access to the backyard. Guests will be amazed by the bold Calacatta gold marble guest bathroom, with large walk-in shower featuring hex tile, plus chevron marble floors, all new designer lighting and marble top vanity. A proper bedroom, perfect for guests or home office completes the first floor. Upstairs you'll find three sizable bedrooms, including a bright and airy principal suite with custom walk-in closet and striking ensuite boasting dual vanity, soaking tub with separate shower, beautifully accented by blush zellige wall tile and handmade painted Anthropologie cement floor tile. The eye-catching hall bath showcases jade wall tile and encaustic cement floor tile with dual vanity, designer lighting, brushed brass detail and shower over deep tub. Hallway hosts convenient second floor side by side laundry. The large tiered backyard, freshly landscaped, is flush with mature fruit trees and a rec room with beamed ceilings and fireplace. Centrally located minutes from Jon & Vinny's, Hilltop Coffee, Simply Wholesome and many other neighborhood favorites. Easily access the 10 and 405 freeways, LAX, the Expo Line and the beach.

Paris , FR
3 Beds - 3 Baths
1,582sqft
$2,247,312

A collector's loft in a remarkable building near Parc Monceau.
This contemporary loft is located on the top floor of a former industrial building built in 1889 to house the Patin coffee roasting plant, and was converted into apartments in 1981, then was listed as a historical monument in 2021.
With a total of 147 m² (125.32 m² Loi Carrez), boasting an entrance hall, 3 bedrooms and 3 bathrooms, featuring an impressive 52 m² reception and exhibition space with 6 m high ceilings with  a lounge and dining room under a zenithal Eiffel glass skylight and original arched windows which flood the space with natural light, a fully-equipped Corian® kitchen, Boffi bathrooms, and an open loft office. Covered parking and concierge complete this one of a kind offering, located on one the most charming streets of Paris, famous for it’s open markets and artisan boutiques.

Welcome to your oasis in the sky. This stunning home is perched atop the exclusive Doheny Estates, offering breathtaking views from the city to the Pacific Ocean and beyond. With 4 beds, 5 baths, and 3,248 sqft of living space, this spacious home is perfect for families or anyone who loves to entertain. Upon entrance, you will be struck by the spaciousness and sophistication of this contemporary home. The open-concept layout and floor-to-ceiling windows create a seamless flow between indoor and outdoor living spaces, making it easy to enjoy the gorgeous views from every room. The gourmet kitchen is a chef's dream with top-of-the-line appliances, spacious countertops, and plenty of storage space. The living room is the perfect place to relax and entertain, with a sleek fireplace and a built-in media center. The spacious primary suite is a true retreat with a walk-in closet and a spa-like bathroom complete with a soaking tub. The two additional bedrooms are also generously sized with their own private bathrooms. Outside, the beautifully landscaped yard offers a peaceful oasis where you can relax and unwind. This home has been meticulously maintained and is in move-in ready condition. Don't miss your chance to enjoy this beautiful property with one-of-a-kind views.
It’s “How did this person afford this trip to Europe?” Month

$2,595,000

In the heart of a magnificent forest, nestled in the "mid-slope" overlooking Chiavenna nearby Lake Como, lies Chalet del Silenzio, a stunning eco-friendly compound, re-imagined vintage mountain cabins with an emphasis on design and sustainability.

Situated in a serene and secure location, encompassed by 7.5 acres of land, this property exudes harmony and respect for nature, and features a main residence and 3 separate cottages.

Every element of the main building and outdoor furniture has been meticulously crafted using reclaimed materials sourced from present materials on site or from trees harvested and processed within the location. Once you step into one of the 3 quaint cabins, a sense of tranquility washes over you. Here, the perfect blend of nature, design, and technology creates a retreat that feels instantly welcoming. Equipped with an environmentally friendly heating/cooling system powered by a heat pump with state-of-the-art black photovoltaic panels coupled with a salt storage battery, ensuring minimal environmental impact.

Located just ten kilometers away from Gordona, with convenient access via private transportation, an active ride share service in Gordona, helicopter, or private driver services from the Milan  airports. 

A one of a kind experience of tranquility, harmony, and breathtaking views, minutes from vibrant Lake Como and famed Saint Moritz snow resort.

David Freedman AIA Architectural mid century modern built in 1959 and fully restored by Casa 24. Located in the Laurelwood Estates development, near Mulholland on a quiet cut de sac, this house was owned by the same family for over fifty years. The original blueprint provided details that the architect intended but until now had not been completed, such as the travertine slab fireplace, poured terrazzo entry and angled patios to create individual seating areas. The entrance features an aggregate patio with a private garden surrounded by breeze block. The spacious kitchen is equipped with Viking appliances, a wine fridge and large island for casual dining. Oak chevron flooring compliments the custom walnut cabinetry throughout the house and the media room’s walnut sliding panel privacy doors. Expansive glass doors open onto the California native landscaped yard, with plans for a pool already approved by the city. The master bedroom features a walk in closet with walnut cabinetry and doors that lead to its own patio. The side patio features a bonus space being used as a gym with a Tonal system and perfect for yoga. Set behind gates with a two car garage, EV charger and security system with cameras. In the award winning Carpenter school district, close to Fryman Canyon hiking trials, and with easy access to both sides of the hill.
